[Scene 1 | 0–5s]
"How does AI actually understand language?"
"Not just words… but meaning between the lines."
"Let me show you the secret behind ChatGPT."

[Scene 2 | 5–15s]
"Take this sentence:"
"'The bank by the river.'"
"Wait… what does 'bank' mean here?"
"A money bank… or the side of a river?"

[Scene 3 | 15–30s]
"Humans use context naturally."
"But how does AI do it?"
"Using something called Self-Attention."
"Where every word looks at every other word."

[Scene 4 | 30–50s]
"Each word gets three roles:"
"Query — what am I looking for?"
"Key — what do I match with?"
"Value — what information do I carry?"

[Scene 5 | 50–70s]
"Now comes the magic."
"Each word compares its Query with all other Keys."
"This creates attention scores — showing relevance."
"And suddenly… 'bank' connects strongly to 'river'."

[Scene 6 | 70–90s]
"These scores are used to combine information."
"So 'bank' is no longer ambiguous."
"It now understands: river bank."

[Scene 7 | 90–105s]
"And this happens for EVERY word…"
"All at the same time."
"That’s how AI understands entire sentences instantly."

[Scene 8 | 105–115s]
"That’s Self-Attention."
"The core idea behind modern AI."

[Scene 9 | 115–120s]
"Thanks for watching!"
"Subscribe for more AI explained simply."